The Centre for Innovative Educational and Communication Technology was torched in the early hours of Tuesday morning. CAPE TOWN The University of the Western Cape has opened a case of arson and theft following an attack on a building at the Bellville campus.The Centre for Innovative Educational and Communication Technology was torched in the early hours of Tuesday morning.About 18 computers were also stolen from a lab next to a university residence.The circumstances are under investigation.(Edited by Masechaba Sefularo)